      <section eId="sec_CCRP-930-5">
        <num>CCRP 930.5</num>
        <heading>930.5.  Custody pending retrial; bail</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-930-5__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If a court grants relief under an application for post conviction relief, the court
shall order that the petitioner be held in custody pending a new trial.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-930-5__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In such a case, the petitioner shall be entitled to bail on the offense as though he
has not been convicted of the offense.
Added by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112946</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
